headline: Dollar Tree Stock Rises. Why Wall Street Likes the Chain’s Long-Term Outlook.
summary: Shares of  Dollar Tree  rose sharply Wednesday after the discount retailer released an upbeat earnings outlook for the next three years.  In numbers released Wednesday, Dollar Tree forecast 12% to 15% annual per-share earnings growth from fiscal 2026 to 2028, headlined by high-teens growth in 2026.  Fellow discount retailer  Dollar General  rose 1.1%.

headline: Dollar Tree Rises After Seeing Earnings Growth Through 2028
summary: Dollar Tree, which made this projection ahead of an investor presentation slated for later on Wednesday, is trying to sharpen its focus under Chief Executive Officer Mike Creedon after selling the struggling Family Dollar chain for about $1 billion.  Jefferies analysts said they remain cautious, calling the company’s overhaul “messy” with only two of 16 officers remaining at Dollar Tree since early 2023.

headline: 73% of U.S. Consumers Plan to Shop at Discount Retailers This Holiday Season: VTEX Commerce
summary: NEW YORK, October 15, 2025--Nearly three-quarters (73%) of U.S. consumers say they plan to shop at discount retailers such as Dollar General, Dollar Tree, and Five Below this holiday season, according to new research from VTEX (NYSE: VTEX), the enterprise commerce platform.
